org.semanticweb.rulewerk.core.model.api

Interface PrefixDeclarationRegistry

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Iterable<Map.Entry<String,String>>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractPrefixDeclarationRegistry, LocalPrefixDeclarationRegistry, MergingPrefixDeclarationRegistry

    public interface PrefixDeclarationRegistry
extends Iterable<Map.Entry<String,String>>
    Registry that manages prefixes and base namespace declarations as used for parsing and serialising inputs.
    Author:
    Markus Kroetzsch

    • Method Detail

      • clear

        void clear()
        Resets the registry to an empty state, without a base or any prefixes.

      • getBaseIri

        String getBaseIri()
        Returns the relevant base namespace. This should always return a result, possibly using a local default value if no base was declared.
        Returns:
        string of an absolute base IRI

      • setBaseIri

        void setBaseIri(String baseIri)
         throws PrefixDeclarationException
        Sets the base namespace to the given value. This should only be done once, and not after the base namespace was assumed to be an implicit default value.
        Parameters:
        baseIri - the new base namespace
        Throws:
        PrefixDeclarationException - if base was already defined

      • getPrefixIri

        String getPrefixIri(String prefixName)
             throws PrefixDeclarationException
        Returns the IRI associated with a given prefix name.
        Parameters:
        prefixName - the name of the prefix.
        Throws:
        PrefixDeclarationException - if prefixName was not defined.

      • setPrefixIri

        void setPrefixIri(String prefixName,
                  String prefixIri)
           throws PrefixDeclarationException
        Registers a prefix declaration. Behaviour is implementation-defined if prefixName has already been registered.
        Parameters:
        prefixName - the name of the prefix.
        prefixIri - the IRI of the prefix.
        Throws:
        PrefixDeclarationException - when prefixName is already registered, at the discretion of the implementation.

      • unsetPrefix

        void unsetPrefix(String prefixName)
        Un-registers a prefix declaration if present.
        Parameters:
        prefixName - the name of the prefix.

      • resolvePrefixedName

        String resolvePrefixedName(String prefixedName)
                    throws PrefixDeclarationException
        Turn a prefixed name into an absolute IRI.
        Parameters:
        prefixedName - a prefixed name of the form prefixName:localName.
        Returns:
        an absolute IRI corresponding to prefixedName.
        Throws:
        PrefixDeclarationException - when the prefixName has not been declared.

      • absolutizeIri

        String absolutizeIri(String relativeOrAbsoluteIri)
              throws PrefixDeclarationException
        Turn a potentially relative IRI into an absolute IRI.
        Parameters:
        relativeOrAbsoluteIri - an IRI that may be relative or absolute.
        Returns:
        when relativeOrAbsoluteIri is an absolute IRI, it is returned as-is. Otherwise, the current base IRI is prepended.
        Throws:
        PrefixDeclarationException - when relativeOrAbsoluteIri is not a valid IRI.

      • unresolveAbsoluteIri

        String unresolveAbsoluteIri(String iri,
                            boolean addIriBrackets)
        Turn an absolute IRI into a (possibly) prefixed name. Dual to resolvePrefixedName(java.lang.String).
        Parameters:
        iri - an absolute IRI to abbreviate
        addIriBrackets - if true, unabbreviated IRIs will be enclosed in < >
        Returns:
        an abbreviated form of iri if an appropriate prefix is known, or iri.
